snippet.textDisplay: I did this on a ford 9", the heat from the welding softened the gears enough that when l really needed it, it stripped the splines off both axles. I was dead in the water. Lol. Then l heard about filling the gears with molten aluminum. The extra weight in negligible, and the alloy doesnt hold enough heat to damage the heat treating of the gears. Best of all, if one wants to undo it, you simply heat it and the aluminum melts out. Just melt the aluminum into the gears with a torch, like melting candle wax. Its very easy!
